1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nd5 4. Bg3 Qb6 5. c4 { Counterattacking our knight. This is actually a good move, but it wouldn't be most people's first thought, so it's quite rare. } { [%csl Rd5][%cal Gc4d5] } 5... Nf6 (5... Qxb2 6. cxd5 Qxa1 7. Qc2 { We're up an exchange but our queen is at risk of being trapped. This is still highly unclear, but not my cup of tea. } { [%csl Ra1] }) 6. Nc3 Qxb2 { Okay, now I'll take. } 7. Nb5? (7. Nge2 cxd4 8. exd4 e6 { White has enough compensation for the pawn, but not more. } { [%cal Gf8b4] }) 7... Qb4+ 8. Qd2 Qxd2+ 9. Kxd2 Ne4+ 10. Kd3 Nxg3 11. hxg3 Na6 { In this endgame White doesn't really have any compensation for the pawn. } *


