{ I'm immediately drawn to the idea of 1. Bxd5 Qxd5 2. Nc3, intending d5. After any queen move, d5 appears to be winning. 2... Nxd4 3. Nxd5 Nxe2 4. Nxc7+ appears to be winning easily as well. What about 1... Nxd4? Then just 2. Nxd4 Qxd5 leaves me up a piece. Are there any other tries for Black? 2... Qc4 3. d5 still seems to work. This seems a bit too simple so I have a feeling I'm missing something, but I would go with Bxd5 intending Nc3 and d5. }
