1. e4 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 1... c6 { I decided to try out the Caro Kann because I'm helping a student with it. } { [%clk 0:30:00] } 2. d4 { [%clk 0:30:07] } 2... d5 { [%clk 0:30:09] } 3. exd5 { [%clk 0:30:24] } 3... cxd5 { [%clk 0:30:25] } 4. Nf3 { [%clk 0:30:40] } 4... Nc6 { [%clk 0:30:42] } 5. Bb5 { [%clk 0:30:57] } 5... Bg4 { [%clk 0:30:57] } 6. h3 { [%clk 0:31:15] } 6... Bxf3 { You're supposed to take here, this much I knew from Alex Banzea videos! } { [%clk 0:31:13] } (6... Bh5 7. g4 Bg6 8. Ne5 { is annoying. } { [%cal Gb5e8,Ge5g6,Gh3h5] }) 7. Qxf3 { But now I realized I didn't know how I should develop. } { [%clk 0:31:35] } 7... e6 { It appears GMs usually prefer to try to take advantage of the bishop on b5 immediately. } { [%clk 0:31:26] } (7... Qa5+ 8. Nc3 e6) (7... a6) 8. O-O { [%clk 0:31:18] } 8... Bd6 { [%clk 0:31:03] } 9. c3 { [%clk 0:30:27] } 9... Ne7 { I believe this is a mistake, and the knight would be better placed on f6. } { [%clk 0:31:12] } (9... h6 { [%cal Gg8f6] }) 10. Re1 { [%clk 0:28:54] } 10... O-O { [%clk 0:31:24] } 11. Nd2 { [%clk 0:27:58] } 11... Rc8 { [%clk 0:31:15] } 12. Qh5 { [%clk 0:25:27] } 12... g6 { [%clk 0:30:53] } 13. Qe2 { [%clk 0:24:42] } 13... Bf4 { Artificial looking move, but I was concerned about Nf3, Bh6, etc. } { [%clk 0:29:03] } 14. Nf3 { [%clk 0:24:32] } 14... Bxc1 { [%clk 0:29:21] } 15. Raxc1 { [%clk 0:24:44] } 15... Nf5 { [%clk 0:29:15] } 16. Bd3 { [%clk 0:23:36] } 16... Nd6 { [%clk 0:29:29] } 17. h4 { [%clk 0:22:11] } 17... Qf6 { [%clk 0:27:06] } (17... h5 { The computer likes this, but I was concerned about later sacrifices on g6 or e6. It's difficult to make a move like this. }) 18. Qd2 { [%clk 0:19:54] } 18... b5 { [%clk 0:25:20] } 19. h5 { [%clk 0:18:51] } 19... Rc7 { [%clk 0:21:11] } 20. hxg6 { [%clk 0:15:28] } 20... hxg6 { [%clk 0:21:24] } 21. Qh6 { Good move, otherwise I would play Kg7. } { [%clk 0:14:01] } 21... Rfc8 { [%clk 0:20:06] } 22. Ne5 { [%clk 0:09:28] } 22... Qg7 { [%clk 0:20:01] } 23. Qh2 { [%clk 0:06:53] } 23... Nxe5 { [%clk 0:18:08] } (23... Nxd4 24. Nxg6 { I didn't want any part of this. }) 24. dxe5 { [%clk 0:04:25] } 24... Nc4 { [%clk 0:18:17] } 25. Rc2 { [%clk 0:03:45] } 25... g5? { Even though I played somewhat aimlessly, it wasn't until I weakened my own king that I really got into trouble. } { [%clk 0:11:54] } (25... a5) 26. f4! { I underestimated this move. } { [%clk 0:03:11] } 26... gxf4 { [%clk 0:07:52] } (26... Qh8 { The computer thinks this is still okay for Black, but no one is going to do this. }) 27. Qxf4 { Both kings are open, but it is White who has the piece activity to do something about it. } { [%clk 0:02:55] } 27... Kf8 { [%clk 0:08:11] } 28. b3! { [%clk 0:02:00] } 28... Nb6 { [%clk 0:07:58] } (28... Na3 29. Qb4+ { [%cal Gb4a3,Gb4f8] }) 29. Bxb5 { [%clk 0:02:03] } 29... d4 { Just trying to survive at this point. } { [%clk 0:07:07] } 30. Qxd4 { [%clk 0:01:52] } 30... Nd5 { [%clk 0:07:25] } 31. c4 { [%clk 0:01:38] } 31... Ne7 { [%clk 0:07:13] } 32. Re4 { [%clk 0:01:19] } (32. Rf2 Nf5 33. Rxf5 exf5 34. Bd7 { would have been a nice way to keep control. }) 32... Nf5 { [%clk 0:07:21] } 33. Qd1 { [%clk 0:01:21] } 33... Rc5 { [%clk 0:07:12] } 34. Rd2 { [%clk 0:01:32] } 34... Qg5 { [%clk 0:07:17] } 35. Rg4? { He finally makes a mistake in time pressure. } { [%clk 0:01:36] } 35... Qe3+ { [%clk 0:07:25] } 36. Kh1 { [%clk 0:01:20] } (36. Kh2 Qxe5+ 37. Kg1 Qe3+ { Apparently Black has nothing better than a repetition. }) 36... Ng3+ { [%clk 0:06:55] } 37. Kh2 { [%clk 0:01:30] } (37. Rxg3 Qxg3 38. Rd8+ Kg7 { should be winning for Black. }) 37... Qxd2 { Tactics! } { [%clk 0:07:14] } 38. Rg8+ { [%clk 0:01:06] } 38... Kxg8 { [%clk 0:07:20] } 39. Qg4+ { [%clk 0:01:22] } 39... Kf8 { [%clk 0:07:38] } 40. Qh4 { [%clk 0:00:48] } 40... Nf1+ { [%clk 0:06:14] } 41. Kh1 { [%clk 0:01:02] } 41... Ng3+ { [%clk 0:05:37] } 42. Kh2 { [%clk 0:01:15] } 42... Nh5 { [%clk 0:05:57] } 43. Qxh5 { [%clk 0:01:19] } 43... Qf4+ { [%clk 0:06:14] } 44. Kh1 { [%clk 0:01:25] } 44... Qxe5 { 0-1 White resigns. } { [%clk 0:06:25] } 0-1


