{ [%evp 0,63,29,19,24,19,18,19,59,49,50,65,63,78,78,78,81,69,54,60,47,51,75,71,
95,60,63,69,67,36,46,54,51,25,23,25,62,46,74,74,65,75,65,51,68,78,91,63,61,72,
50,10,182,202,207,196,584,584,801,947,1441,29982,29983,29984,29993,29994] }
1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c6 4. e3 Bf5 5. f3 e6 6. g4 Bg6 7. h4 h5 { This line is
very common for Black players who don't have specific preparation vs. the
Jobava. } 8. g5 Nfd7 9. Bd3 (9. Nh3!?) (9. Nge2!?) 9... Bxd3 10. cxd3 { I saw Jobava do this in a blitz game. The computer does not approve. } (10. Qxd3) 10... g6 11. Nge2 Bg7 12. Qc2 (12. O-O { Computer wants to go kingside but it
looks scary. }) 12... e5? (12... Na6 { staying flexible. }) 13. dxe5 Nxe5 14. Bxe5! { Good choice to eliminate the strong knight. } 14... Bxe5 15. d4 Bg7 16. O-O-O (16. f4 { The computer loves this idea. Didn't consider it at all. } { [%cal Rf4f5] } 16... Qe7 17. f5 Qxe3 18. Nxd5) 16... O-O 17. Kb1 { Objectively too casual, but in rapid I think it's okay. } 17... Qe7 18. e4 dxe4 19. fxe4 Na6 20. Nf4 (20. e5 { What I wanted to play, but... } 20... Nb4 21. Qb3 c5 { ...couldn't see what to do here. Computer says it's still good
for White. } 22. Nf4 { [%cal Rb3g8,Rf4g6] } 22... Kh8 23. Rhe1 cxd4 24. Rxd4 Nc6 25. Rde4) 20... Rad8 21. e5 Nc7 22. Ne4 Nd5 23. Nf6+! Bxf6 (23... Kh8 24. Qxg6 { I was hoping for this one. }) 24. gxf6 Qc7 25. Nxh5! (25. Nxg6 fxg6 26. Qxg6+ Kh8 27. Qxh5+ Qh7+ { Not clear at all. }) (25. Nxd5 Rxd5 26. Rhg1 Kh7 27. Rg5 { This might have been a simpler solution. }) 25... Kh7 26. Ng7 Ne3 27. Qe4 Nxd1 28. h5 Kg8 (28... Nf2 29. hxg6+ Kg8 30. Rh8+ Kxh8 31. Qh4+ Kg8 32. Qh7#) 29. hxg6 fxg6 30. Qxg6 Nc3+ 31. bxc3 Qb6+ 32. Ka1 { NateSolon won on time Nice
attacking game. You handled the middlegame complications well. It sucks that
this very common line agains the Jobava doesn't seem to have a good solution. } 1-0


