1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4 3. Bf4 c5 4. f3 Qa5+ 5. c3 Nf6 6. d5 (6. Nd2 { I sensed he would be more comfortable with the forcing lines here. }) 6... d6 7. e4 e6 8. Na3 (8. dxe6 Bxe6 9. Bxd6 (9. Na3! { I only connected dxe6 with
grabbing the pawn, but the computer loves this for White, perhaps planning to
pick up d6 later. }) 9... Bxd6 10. Qxd6 Nc6 { I correctly wanted no
part of this. } { [%cal Ra8d8] }) 8... exd5 9. exd5 Be7 10. Nc4 Qc7 11. a4 O-O 12. Ne2 Nh5 13. Be3 Re8 14. g4! { Great choice! } 14... Bh4+ 15. Bf2 Bxf2+ 16. Kxf2 Nf6 17. Ng3 { I correctly evaluated this as crushing for White. His problem is he can't get
out the queenside pieces. } 17... h6 (17... Nbd7 18. g5 { [%csl Rf6] }) 18. h4 Nh7 19. Bd3 Nf8 20. Ne4? { Wrong idea! Pawn grabbing when you should be checkmating. } (20. g5! { The attack is crushing. }) 20... Ng6 21. Nexd6 Rd8 22. Bxg6 fxg6 23. Nxc8 Qxc8 24. Qd3 Nd7 25. g5 (25. Qxg6 { Not exactly sure what I didn't like
about this. } 25... Nf6 26. d6 Qe6 27. Rhe1 Qxc4 28. Re7) 25... Nf8 26. Rae1 Qd7 27. d6 Re8 28. Qd5+ Kh7 29. gxh6 gxh6 30. Ne5 Qf5 31. Qxb7+ Kg8 32. Qd5+ Kg7 33. Qb7+ Kg8 34. Nc6 { Still winning, but I don't like how your pieces have drifted
away from the center and your king. } 34... Qc2+ 35. Kg3 Rxe1 36. Rxe1 Qd2 37. Qe7 (37. Ne7+ { Forcing solution } 37... Kh8 38. Nxg6+ { Missed this one. } 38... Nxg6 39. Qxa8+) 37... g5 38. hxg5 hxg5 39. Re4 Rc8 40. Ne5 Qd1 41. Qxg5+ { NateSolon won on
time Played the opening very well. Missed a clean win by going pawn grabbing
when you could have just checkmated him. Objectively never lost the win, but
definitely lost control. } 1-0


