1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 (3. Nc3 Nc6 4. Bb5 (4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Nxe4 6. Nxe4 (6. Nxc6 Nxc3 7. Nxd8 Nxd1 8. Nxf7 Kxf7 (8... Nxf2? 9. Nxh8 Nxh1 10. Be3 { White may be able to save his knight while winning the Black knight. } { [%csl Rh1] }) 9. Bc4+ Kf6 10. Kxd1 (10. h4!? b5! 11. Bd3 (11. Bxb5? Rb8! { The knight escapes! }) 11... Nxf2 12. Kxf2 Bc5+ 13. Kg3 Bd6+ 14. Bf4 Bxf4+ 15. Kxf4 Bb7) 10... c6 { [%cal Gd7d5] }) 6... Qe7 7. f3 d5 8. Bb5 Bd7 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. O-O dxe4 11. Re1 O-O-O) 4... Nd4) (3. d4) 3... d5 4. exd5 (4. d4 { Forces a transposition back to main lines. } 4... Nxe4 5. Bd3 Nd7 6. Nxd7 Bxd7 7. O-O Bd6 8. Nc3 (8. c4) 8... Qh4!? { I like
this rare move. } (8... Nxc3 9. bxc3 O-O (9... h5!?) 10. Qh5 f5 11. Re1 { Black is under a bit of pressure, but should hold with precise play. } 11... c6 12. Bg5 Qc7) 9. g3 Nxc3 10. bxc3 Qh3 11. Re1+ Be6 12. Bf1 (12. Rb1 { Stockfish
thinks this is very promising for White. }) 12... Qf5 13. Bd3 { White can force
a draw. } 13... Qh3) 4... Qxd5 5. d4 (5. Qe2 Bc5?! (5... Be7 6. Nc3 Qd8) (5... Be6 6. Nc3) 6. Ng6+ Be6 7. Nxh8 Nc6 { Winning for White, but terrifying. } { [%csl Rh8][%cal Ge8c8,Gc6d4] }) (5. Nf3 Bg4 6. Be2 Bd6 7. O-O Qh5) 5... Nc6 6. Nxc6 Qxc6 (6... bxc6? 7. Be2 Qxg2 8. Bf3) 7. Qe2+ (7. Nc3 Bb4 (7... Be6?? 8. Bb5)) 7... Be7 (7... Be6) (7... Kd8!?) 8. Qb5 O-O 9. Qxc6 bxc6 { [%cal Gc6c5,Gf8d8] } *


