1. e4 { [%clk 0:05:00] } 1... e5 { [%clk 0:05:00] } 2. Nf3 { [%clk 0:04:59] } 2... Nc6 { [%clk 0:04:59] } 3. Bb5 { [%clk 0:04:57] } 3... Qf6? $146 { This is a classic case of bringing out the queen too early. } { [%clk 0:04:57] } 4. Nc3! { Good reaction - the knight heads to d5 where it will hit the queen. } { [%cal Gc3d5,Gd5f6,Gd5c7] [%clk 0:04:55] } 4... Bc5 { [%clk 0:04:53] } 5. Nd5 { [%clk 0:04:50] } 5... Qd6 { [%clk 0:04:51] } 6. c3! { Another good move, preparing d4. } { [%cal Gd2d4] [%clk 0:04:45] } 6... Nge7 { [%clk 0:04:50] } 7. d4 { [%clk 0:04:20] } 7... Bb6 { [%cal Gd4e5] [%clk 0:04:48] } (7... exd4 8. Bf4 { [%csl Rc7][%cal Gf4c7,Gd5c7] }) 8. dxe5? { So far White has played perfectly, but this is a mistake. Better was simply castling. Black can't resolve the tension in the center - both possible captures would lose. But this means it's almost impossible for Black to develop the queenside. } { [%clk 0:04:09] } (8. O-O! { [%csl Rc8,Ra8] } 8... Nxd5 (8... exd4 9. Bf4) 9. exd5 Qxd5 10. c4 Qd6 (10... Qe6 11. d5) 11. c5 $18) 8... Nxe5 { [%clk 0:04:43] } 9. Bf4 { [%clk 0:04:05] } 9... Nxd5 { [%clk 0:04:35] } 10. Bxe5 { [%clk 0:03:52] } 10... Qc5 { Gaining a tempo by threatening mate. Objectively White is still better, but it's messy. This is why it's a good idea to castle early even if your king doesn't seem to be immediately threatened. } { [%cal Gc5f2] [%clk 0:04:33] } 11. O-O { [%clk 0:02:15] } 11... Nxc3 { [%clk 0:04:05] } 12. Bxc3 { [%clk 0:01:49] } 12... Qxb5 { [%clk 0:04:03] } 13. Bxg7 { [%clk 0:01:42] } (13. a4! { Going after the bishop, not an easy move to spot } { [%cal Ga4a5] } 13... Qh5 14. a5 Bc5 15. Bxg7 Rg8 16. Be5 { [%cal Ge5g3] }) 13... Rg8 { [%clk 0:03:59] } 14. Bc3? { [%clk 0:01:21] } (14. Be5 { It was important to use the bishop to plug the g-file. } { [%cal Ge5g3] }) 14... d6 { All of a sudden Black has an initiative on the kingside. } { [%cal Gg8g2,Gc8h3] [%clk 0:03:57] } 15. e5? { Not realizing the initiative has passed over to Black and it's time for damage control. } { [%clk 0:01:13] } 15... Bg4 { [%clk 0:03:52] } 16. exd6 { [%clk 0:01:11] } 16... O-O-O! { [%clk 0:03:49] } 17. a4 { [%clk 0:00:18] } 17... Qh5 { 0-1 Black wins on time. } { [%clk 0:03:35] } 0-1


