1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. Bxc6 { Trading off the bishop at this moment doesn't make a ton of sense, but it's pretty popular at the club level. } 4... dxc6 { Opening up our bishop. } { [%cal Gc8g4] } 5. O-O Nxe4 { Continuing our strategy of grabbing e4 when given the chance. } 6. Re1 Nd6 7. Nxe5 Be7 { Black has the bishop pair and an ultra-solid position. } { [%cal Ge8g8,Gc8e6] } *


